description_0: A wall with 2 mounted fish taxidermy models in display, The fish both face the right side with their mouths open, they are stacked vertically and have metallic wings by their gills. The fish on top is smaller than below and has a white underbelly while the other has a more green tone to it. Below the fish is a framed image of another fish facing to the left, the fish has large fins and below it is a text that reads "MALOLO PUHIKII" and "PAREXOCOETUS BRACHYPTERUS." The frame sits on a wooden surface angled on an olive green wall to the left of a hand sanitizer dispenser.
description_1: A high-angle view of a stuffed toy of a trout hanging face down. It has light gray, light red, baby blue, and sage green stripe patterns on its scales going from left to right. The top fins are sage green and the bottom fins are light orange with a sage green tail. The trout is hanging on a light gray wooden post with scratches on it, causing the light brown wood to peak through. On the left, there is a light-oak shelf filled with olive green and white stuffed animals stacked on each other. A silver metallic container is placed above. A brown barrel is next to the trout.
